column3: Catholics eye charges vs CCP over 'blasphemous' art exhibit08/02/2011 | 05:51 PM     Lay Catholic groups are considering filing charges against the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City over what they called a ﾓsacrilegious and blasphemous"" art exhibit.Pro-Life Philippines sent a letter to the CCP and the artists who claimed to be from the University of Santo Tomas (UST) and demanded that the exhibit ﾓKulo"" be stopped by Thursday.ﾓBy Thursday afternoon
column4: we will file a case if they do not stop the exhibit and if they do not also make amends because stopping is not enough. The damage has been done
column5: Eric Manalang
column6: president of Pro-life Philippines
column7: said in an article posted on the Catholic Bishopsﾒ Conference of the Philippines news site on Tuesday.GMA News Online has tried but was unable to reach the CCP and the UST for comment as of posting time.Controversial exhibitThe exhibit ﾓKulo"" will run from July 17 to August 21.Lay groups said the exhibit mocks the Catholic religion because the ﾓcontroversial"" collage ﾓPoleteismo"" done by UST-trained artist Medio Cruz illustrates:A religious image of Jesus Christ. Attached to the religious image is a wooden replica of the male genital protruding toward His face. The male genital replica is draped with the Rosary
column8: hanging by the base and top of the replica. To a crucifix is attached a red male organ.A similar religious image of Christ
column9: where His eyes are darkened by black ink which appears to flow out from the eyes.A crucifix and cross draped with a pink
column10: stretched-out condom.Various religious images and pictures of Christ
column11: Mary the Mother of Christ
column12: Holy Family
column14: and the rosary ﾗ all closely surrounded and placed beside pictures of women who appear to be modeling for underwear or a skin product.A picture of Christﾒs disciples surrounding a dark silhouette of Christ in the middle. Right above the facial portion of the dark silhouette of Jesus Christ is a drawing resembling the icon of Disneyﾒs Mickey Mouse.A religious statue of Christ seated. Attached to the tip of His nose is a red ball. Above His head is an imposed pair of red ears the same as Mickey Mouse icon.Violation of Art. 201 of RPCLawyer Jo Imbong
column15: executive director of the St. Thomas More Society (STMS)
column16: an association of Catholic lawyers
column17: said the organizers are liable for violating Revised Penal Codeﾒs (RPC) Article 201 on immortal doctrines
column19: and indecent shows.ﾓMay kaparusahan ﾑyung mga gumagawa ng public exhibit na ang laman ng exhibit ay mga bagay na insulto sa relihiyonﾅ May liability kasi you are offending the religious belief of a country [with] 85 percent Christians
column20: Imbong said in a press statement on Tuesday.Also
column21: in a five-page letter addressed to CCP president Raul Sunico
column22: STMS asked for the closure of the art gallery
column23: or ﾓwe shall be constrained to pursue all forms of judicial relief to restrain the further exhibition of these works.""Imbong warned the Sunico that the CCP executives would be responsible for what the group described as a sickening piece of artwork.Violation of CCP mandateImbong said public display of the collage is in violation of the mandate of the CCP
column24: the countryﾒs premier institution for culture and the arts.The CCP is a public agency so ﾓthe exhibition and hosting of an exhibit hostile to the very mandate of that agency ﾗ on public property and by a public agency ﾗ is an abuse of public authority and a breach of public trust
column25: she stressed.ﾓIt does no public service except to subvert the common good
column26: appealing as it does to the baser instinct rather than to higher and more edifying dispositions of the human person

column29: I am rather detached and objective in my perception of realties
column32: I am filled with anger and disgust

dahil masyado nang mahaba ang thread sa tanong na ito:one of the statements is true. which one is it?A. one statement is falseB. two statements are falseC. three statements are falseD. four statements are falseeto ang sagot/paliwanag/imbento ko. feel free to contradict me kung sa tingin nyo mali. :)eto ay kung mag-stick tayo sa idea na walang sinabi na ""ONLY"" one is true. ganun din sa choices - hindi only 1
column4: only 2
column5: only 3.. bale:(at least) 1 of the statements is true.A. (at least) 1 statement is false  <- A is false if all statements are trueB. (at least) 2 statements are false <- B is false if at at least 3 are trueC. (at least) 3 statements are false <- C is false if at least 2 are trueD. 4 statements are false <--D will always be false dahil may isa ngang true ayon sa tanong.if A is true:D is false
column6: B is true and C is falseif B is true:D is false
column7: C is false
column8: A is trueif C is true:A
column9: B and D should be false.pero di pwedeng false ang A kasi A will only be false if all statements are true.if D is true:naglolokohan lang tau._______________________so ang sagot ko
column10: A or B.

Shylynne Castillo, JOB OPENING: WRITER FOR GOOD GOVERNANCE BOOK The Ateneo School of Government and Kaya Natin! Movement for Good Governance and Ethical Leadership (KN) will be publishing a book on good governance, detailing the lives of some of our government officials practicing effective, ethical, and empowering leadership. As such, we are currently looking for experienced, freelance feature writers who can contribute to the book by writing a profile on one Champion of Good Governance. The project will entail interviews, research, and possibly a trip to the province of the featured individual (if needed). The KN Champions to be featured are Akbayan Rep. Kaka Bag-ao; newly appointed Presidential Adviser on Environmental Protection Neric Acosta, Mayor Jeng Reyes of Alicia, Isabela; former Mayor Jan Disomimba of Tamparan, Lanao del Sur; former Mayor Florante Gerdan of Santa Fe, Nueva Vizcaya; Camarines Sur Provincial Administrator and former Mayor Fermin Mabulo; Mayor Baby Congco of Cabiao, Nueva Ecija; former Councilor Francis Tinio of Binalonan, Pangasinan; Mayor Marivic Belena of San Jose, Nueva Ecija; and former Mayor Mary Jane Ortega of San Fernando, La Union. Minimum requirements are as follows: a.) College graduate of any 4-year courseb.) With extensive writing experiencec.) Good communications/interview and research skillsd.) Willing to travel and learne.) Committed, dedicated, with a passion for good governance and leadership The project will start on September 19, 2011. Deadline for submission of final articles will be on October 19, 2011. Interested applicants must send their resume, a letter of intent explaining why they are interested to be involved in the project, and two (2) sample feature articles. Previously published works are not required, but will be favored. Kindly submit your applications to kai.pastores@gmail.com and shylynne29@yahoo.com on or before Monday, September 12, 2011. Thank you!

While driving on a rural end of the roadway on Thursday morning, I saw an infant car seat on the side of the road with a blanket draped over it. For some reason, I did not stop, even though I had all kinds ... of thoughts running through my head. But when I got to my destination, I called the Police and they were going to check it out. But, this is what the Police advised even before they went out there to check.... "There are several things to be aware of ... gangs and thieves are now plotting different ways to get a person (mostly women)to stop their vehicle and get out of the car. There is a gang initiation reported by the local Police where gangs are placing a car seat by the road...with a fake baby in it...waiting for a woman, of course, to stop and check on the abandoned babyﾔ Note that the location of this car seat is usually beside a wooded or grassy (field) area and the person -- woman -- will be dragged into the woods, beaten and raped, and usually left for dead. Zarah Clariza, Equation 1:Study = Don't FailEquation 2:Don't Study =FailAdding equations 1 and 2:Study + Don't Study = Fail + Don't Fail=> Study (1 + Don't) = Fail (1 + Don't)=> Study = Fail
David Sta Maria, Mathematical proof that studying won't guarantee acing an exam. What if we treat it as an Inequation? Given 1:Study < Don't Fail[Read as: if you study, there is a greater probability that you don't fail]Given 2:Don't Study < Fail[Read as: if you don't study, there is a greater probability that you fail]Adding inequations 1 and 2 we get:Study + Don't Study < Fail + Don't Fail=> Study (1 + Don't) < Fail (1 + Don't)By definition, the value of Don't > or = 0, depending on the obedience of the student [where pasaways do it even if you say Don't]=> Study < FailHence, even if you study, it is more likely you will fail.

column4: we find ourselves dwarfed in comparison
column5: and in some situations
column6: it makes us feel like we're not getting our fair share of what's out there. We search for immortality
column7: we step on others to get a false sense that we're getting anywhere near the impossibility and it's all because we can't get over the fact that some day
column8: we're gonna die and we'd have missed out on a lot of things. The earth is 4.5 billion years old. The sun has been out for longer. And let's not forget other stars and stellar systems that are even older
column9: and we feel even smaller. We are insignificant whatever political dogma we follow
column10: whatever party we join
column11: whatever faction we side with
column12: whatever trivial leap we make in our attempts to rule others. The moment we let go of the artificial borders and barriers we create
column13: the sooner we get to a more fulfilling society. We are getting numb. We need to feel pain. We need to feel happiness and fulfillment. We need to feel something that matters
column14: because one way or another

column3: The Buffalo TheoryA herd of buffalo can only move as fast as the slowest buffalo and when the herd is hunted
column4: it is the slowest and weakest ones at the back that are killed first. This natural selection is good for the herd as a whole
column5: because the general speed and health of the whole group keeps improving by the regular killing of the weakest members. In much the same way
column6: the human brain can only operate as fast as the slowest brain cells. Now
column7: as we know
column8: excessive drinking of alcohol kills brain cells. But naturally
column9: it attacks the slowest and weakest brain cells first. In this way
column10: regular consumption of beer eliminates the weaker brain cells
column11: making the brain a faster and more efficient machine. And that is why you always feel smarter after a few beers.

A Letter from ""Mom n Dad""...My child
column4: When I get old
column5: I hope you understand 'n have patience with meIn case I break the plate
column6: or spill soup on the table because Iﾒm losing my eyesight
column7: I hope you donﾒt yell at me.Older people are sensitive
column8: always having self pity when you yell.When my hearing gets worse 'n I canﾒt hear what youﾒre saying
column9: I hope you donﾒt call me ﾑDeaf!ﾒPlease repeat what you said or write it down.Iﾒm sorry
column10: my child.Iﾒm getting older.When my knees get weaker
column11: I hope you have the patience to help me get up.Like how I used to help you while you were little
column12: learning how to walk.Please bear with me
column13: when I keep repeating myself like a broken record
column14: I hope you just keep listening to me.Please donﾒt make fun of me
column15: or get sick of listening to me.Do you remember when you were little 'n you wanted a ballon? You repeated yourself over 'n over until you get what you wanted.Please also pardon my smell. I smell like an old person.Please donﾒt force me to shower.My body is weak.Old people get sick easily when theyﾒre cold. I hope I donﾒt gross you out.Do you remember when you were little? I used to chase you around because you didnﾒt want to shower.I hope you can be patient with me when Iﾒm always cranky. Itﾒs all part of getting old.Youﾒll understand when youﾒre older.'n if you have spare time
column16: I hope we can talk even for a few minutes.Iﾒm always all by myself all the time
column17: 'n have no one to talk to.I know youﾒre busy with work.Even if youﾒre not interested in my stories
column18: please have time for me.Do you remember when you were little? I used to listen to your stories about your teddy bear.When the time comes
column20: I hope you have the patience to take care of me.Iﾒm sorry if I accidentally wet the bed or make a mess.I hope you have the patience to take care of me during the last few moments of my life.Iﾒm not going to last much longer
column21: anyway.When the time of my death comes
column22: I hope you hold my hand 'n give me strength to face death.'n donﾒt worry..When I finally meet our creator
column23: I will whisper in his ear to bless you. Because you loved your Mom 'n Dad.Thank you so much for your care.We love you. ! <U+2665>""Just Like This Status If You Love It & You Will Never Leave Your Parents At Any Cost""

Boyakzki Romagos, "FACEBOOK PORNOGRAPHY ISSUE"SOLUTION:Simple setting but helpful.I don't know if you all heard about all the mess regarding pornography being placed on thousands of FB users sites.Facebook has changed and said nothing (again).Take a look at your URL (top box on your screen.) If you see "http" or just "www", instead of "https", you DO NOT have a secure session.Go to Account SettingsClick Security on the left top cornerClick Edit next to Secure BrowsingCheck box and lastly,Click Save.FB has automatically set it on the non-secure setting! Do everyone a huge favor, copy this and post in your FB account to prevent the hacking issue

Boyakzki Romagos, I absolutely understand everyone from the university to have a stereotype stance of reaction, whenever the word military is mentioned. A problem that was started by a man, who abused not only this institution of learning, but everything else he wanted to put his grip on. And that is history now. While you, our scholars were busy in your studies to prepare yourselves, not only to be a better citizens, but leaders of our beloved motherland. Your military, were there in the thickest and hinterlands, also busy, in their obligation to secure our peace and rule of law. So, all our country men may be able to finish all their aspirations in life, whatever it might be. Your AFP, is an institution of trained men of discipline,integrity and honor to respect the rule of the civilian over the military. A rule that is almost hard to accept, if you were trained to be free at the onset of your education. While they swllow their pride and start their life of restraint. They now become the instrument of our democracy. Both men are raised up by this country and government inorder for us to survive a better nation. Your men in uniform deserve our trust and respect, as they salute you, our scholars when your time come, as future leaders of our society.19 minutes ago ﾷ Like ﾷ 1
Kevin Jason Manuel, my brother, a com eng'g freshie, wrote this poem. i just thought it was worth sharing.. :)The Dying World see the world end, see it fadeit does not boom, it merely whispersin the rustling of fallen leavesits farewell song: (through all these kind yearsi loved you, for you loved meyou created me with your dreams.but the time is near whenyou will wake upand i will bebut a buried tomb from the past.remember me through your life andway of living, fori will always remember you.) (i was a world ever unfinishedfull of wonder and love andmystery and laughter.i was your life beyond life,but i am fadinggoodbye. i love you, owner.) and each yowie is forgotten,little by little.and each feature, each dreamscape,each fear and oddity,fades into the oblivion of forgetfulness.(that place where all magicmust end) see how old you are growing?(for even black cats and robotsturn into hands and yous) see how more real the world grows for you?but see how we forget this dying world.        (and no amount of power will ever revive it) it is just so sadthat i know by now thatthere will be no finale,no last goodbye hugs and kisses from everyone,from everything, everywhere.for i know how the world ends.(it ends through fallen tearson a pillowcase.it ends with dust under the bedit ends with changing voicesand changing faces.it ends, most of all, with you.you made this world, butso too shall you destroy it.) at least i will end in your sleep.one day, after playing under a bright sunin Omo fields with your beloved bear,night will come, and with it comes sleep,butwhen you awake, you shall no longerplay with your beloved bear.you would have forgotten(all the joysall the endless afternoonsspent under a tree together.)you will forgetforget in your sleep.the world ended when you slept, but i don't blame you,i fell asleep too. this world(a half-unfinished dreamthat ended before you knew it,that you and i will forgetforever?) save --perhaps --for some sleepy nightsin sleepy doctor school dreams,you may remember or hear a voice from long ago,perhaps reminding you to feed the parrots on your head,or to give your liger some crackers. (i love you,goodbye, owner.)

column3: ONIONS ~ MAYONNAISE PLEASE READ TO THE END: IMPORTANTIn 1919 when the flu killed 40 million people there was this Doctor thatvisited the many farmers to see if he could help them combat the flu.Many of the farmers and their family had contracted it and many died.The doctor came upon this one farmer and to his surprise
column4: everyone was very healthy. When the doctor asked what the farmer was doing that was differentthe wife replied that she had placed an unpeeled onion in a dish in therooms of the home
column5: (probably only two rooms back then). The doctor couldn't believe it and asked if he could have one of the onions and place it underthe microscope. She gave him one and when he did this
column6: he did find the fluvirus in the onion. It obviously absorbed the bacteria
column7: therefore
column8: keepingthe family healthy.Now
column9: I heard this story from my hairdresser in AZ. She said that severalyears ago many of her employees were coming down with the flu and so weremany of her customers. The next year she placed several bowls with onionsaround in her shop. To her surprise
column10: none of her staff got sick. It mustwork.. Try it and see what happens. We did it last year and we never got the flu. Now there is a P. S. to this for I sent it to a friend in Oregon whoregularly contributes material to me on health issues. She replied with this most interesting experience about onions:Thanks for the reminder. I don't know about the farmers story.. but
column11: I doknow that I contacted pneumonia and needless to say I was very ill.. I came across an article that said to cut both ends off an onion put it into anempty jar...placing the jar next to the sick patient at night. It said theonion would be black in the morning from the germs.. sure enough it happened just like that.. the onion was a mess and I began to feel better.Another thing I read in the article was that onions and garlic placed aroundthe room saved many from the black plague years ago. They have powerful antibacterial
column12: antiseptic properties.This is the other note.Lots of times when we have stomach problems we don't know what to blame.Maybe it's the onions that are to blame. Onions absorb bacteria is thereason they are so good at preventing us from getting colds and flu's and isthe very reason we shouldn't eat an onion that has been sitting for a timeafter it has been cut open.LEFT OVER ONIONS ARE POISONOUSI had the wonderful privilege of touring Mullins Food Products
column13: Makers of mayonnaise.. Mullins is huge
column14: and is owned by 11 brothers and sisters in the Mullins family. My friend
column15: Jeanne
column16: is the CEO.Questions about food poisoning came up
column17: and I wanted to share what I learned from a chemist.The guy who gave us our tour is named Ed. He's one of the brothers Ed is a chemistry expert and is involved in developing most of the sauce formula.He's even developed sauce formula for McDonald's.Keep in mind that Ed is a food chemistry whiz. During the tour
column18: someoneasked if we really needed to worry about mayonnaise. People are alwaysworried that mayonnaise will spoil. Ed's answer will surprise you. Ed saidthat all commercially- made Mayo is completely safe.""It doesn't even have to be refrigerated. No harm in refrigerating it
column19: butit's not really necessary."" He explained that the pH in mayonnaise is set ata point that bacteria could not survive in that environment. He then talked about the quaint essential picnic
column20: with the bowl of potato salad sitting onthe table and how everyone blames the mayonnaise when someone gets sick.Ed says that! when food poisoning is reported
column21: the first thing the officials look for is when the 'victim' last ate ONIONS and where those onions camefrom (in the potato salad?). Ed says it's not the mayonnaise (as long asit's not homemade Mayo) that spoils in the outdoors. It's probably theonions
column24: onions are a huge magnet for bacteria
column25: especially uncookedonions. You should never plan to keep a portion of a sliced onion.. He saysit's not even safe if you put it in a zip-lock bag and put it in your refrigerator.It's already contaminated enough just by being cut open and out for a bit
column26: that it can be a danger to you (and doubly watch out for those onions youput in your hotdogs at the baseball park!) Ed says if you take the leftover onion and cook it like crazy you'll probably be okay
column27: but if you slice that leftover onion and put on your sandwich
column28: you're asking for trouble. Both the onions and the moist potato in a potato salad
column29: will attract and grow bacteria faster than any commercial mayonnaise will even begin to break down. Also
column30: dogs should never eat onions. Their stomachs cannot metabolize onions.Please remember it is dangerous to cut an onion and try to use it to cook the next day

column4: better known as simply Valentine's Day
column5: is the annual commemoration of love celebrated on February 14. Valentine's Day was created by Pope Gelasius I in 500 AD to honor the Christian martyrs named Valentine. The religious observance of the day was deleted by Pope Paul VI from the Roman calender of saints in 1969 but is still often permitted. Valentine's Day was first related to romantic love by Geoffrey Chaucer during the Middle Ages. column5: please go to PGH Blood Bank (ideally tomorrow) between 6-8AM. Bring with you a valid ID (with signature) and ballpen; and be ready to wait until ~10AM.From Petron Philcoa
